    {
      "text": "A 38-year-old male, a known alcoholic, presents with intermittent epigastric pain for three months, described as a burning sensation occurring mainly after meals. He reports bloating, occasional nausea, and temporary relief with antacids. Upper GI endoscopy reveals peptic ulcers in the gastric antrum. What is the most likely cause of this patient\u2019s gastritis?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Autoimmune destruction of parietal cells",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Helicobacter pylori infection",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Chronic alcohol consumption alone",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Stress-related mucosal injury",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "B. Helicobacter pylori infection",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Feature</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Type B Gastritis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Type A Gastritis</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Cause</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Primarily caused by H. pylori infection and long-term <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"b924074dfe16927771933b6d50eaac\">NSAID</span> use</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Autoimmune condition, often associated with autoantibodies against <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51df38de3d1692777194ced4c4bab5\">parietal</span> cells and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a6795c876e169277719057a1099465\">intrinsic</span> factor</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Location of Inflammation</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Antrum (lower part) of the stomach, near the pylorus</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Fundus (upper part) of the stomach, where <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51df38de3d1692777194ced4c4bab5\">parietal</span> cells are found</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Symptoms</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Epigastric pain, bloating, nausea, vomiting, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"50f4196df6169277720181ef605c33\">ulceration</span> in some cases.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Often asymptomatic, but may cause symptoms like nausea, vomiting, and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1665a40f1016927771801899eaed5d\">abdominal</span> discomfort</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Associated Conditions</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Peptic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">ulcer</span> disease (PUD), <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> cancer risk</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Pernicious <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> (due to vitamin B12 deficiency)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Histological Findings</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Chronic inflammation, increased lymphocytes and neutrophils, often with atrophic changes</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Chronic inflammation, loss of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"51df38de3d1692777194ced4c4bab5\">parietal</span> cells, and often <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"97ff5253fb169277718224c7b0faf8\">atrophy</span> of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> mucosa</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Risk Factors</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><em>H. pylori</em> infection, NSAIDs, alcohol, smoking</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Autoimmunity, genetic predisposition, vitamin B12 deficiency</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Treatment</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Eradication of <em>H. pylori</em> with antibiotics and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9c823198d61692777196bc71097d6d\">proton</span> pump inhibitors (PPIs)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Vitamin B12 supplementation and immune modulation; PPIs may also be used</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Prognosis</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>If untreated, it can lead to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f6768ff15f1692777195a493cad3a9\">peptic</span> ulcers and an increased risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> cancer.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>If untreated, it can result in <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"5cc1ea37091692777195fbd0aa687b\">pernicious</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"53bee2a41216927771814d7ec3a67f\">anemia</span> and an increased risk of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> carcinoma.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
