      "text": "A 42-year-old man presents with a 4-week history of burning epigastric pain that occurs 1-2 hours after meals and is temporarily relieved by food. He also complains of vomiting. On examination, his heart rate is 115 beats per minute, and his temperature is 98.6\u00b0F. Mild epigastric tenderness is noted, and laboratory tests show mild anemia. What is the most likely diagnosis?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Duodenal ulcer",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Acute pancreatitis",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Gastric ulcer",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Gastroesophageal reflux disease",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "A. Duodenal ulcer",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:NaN\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Gastric <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">Ulcer</span> (GU)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Duodenal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">Ulcer</span> (DU)</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Common risk factors </strong>for both GU and DU: H. pylori, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"867d774b951692777190c8cfebd37a\">indiscriminate</span> use of NSAIDS due to comorbidities in the patients like <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"720567fecd169277719411dda3d1a2\">osteoarthritis</span> or requiring total knee replacement, etc.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>> 6th-decade</li>\n<li>Premalignant condition.</li>\n<li>MC site: Lesser <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4bd67d54f016927771850c953dadbc\">curvature</span> of stomach.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Basal/Nocturnal acid production: \u2191</li>\n<li>MC site: First part of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"280e59e9331692777186f3beac2c41\">duodenum</span> or duodenal cap, usually within 3 cm of the pylorus.</li>\n<li>Size of Ulcer: <1 cm.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Pain Pattern:</strong> Pain is <strong>precipitated by</strong> food.</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Pain Pattern:</strong> Pain occurs 90 min to 3 h after a meal and is <strong>relieved by</strong> food or antacids.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Common Features:</strong></p>\n<ol>\n<li>Epigastric pain (gnawing or burning sensation)</li>\n<li>Epigastric tenderness</li>\n<li>Tachycardia and Orthostasis caused by:</li>\n</ol>\n<ul>\n<li>Vomiting, may be due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4f75cbe5e8169277719615b86767c9\">pylorospasm</span> or local edema</li>\n<li>GI bleeding</li>\n</ul>\n<ol>\n<li>Rigidity in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1ba6a9cfe11692777181950edd7a6d\">anterior</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"1665a40f1016927771801899eaed5d\">abdominal</span> wall is suggestive of perforation</li>\n<li>Succussion splash: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">Gastric</span> outlet <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"39f44b27bf169277719416f29a74ee\">obstruction</span> (due to pyloric stenosis, pylorospasm, or local <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"18b452e75916927771864c9ad533e1\">edema</span> due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">ulcer</span> in the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"13da15e2e41692777195755a5d4357\">peripyloric</span> area or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"21e2d5a70616927772021fcdec0ca9\">fibrosis</span> extending to the duodenum).</li>\n</ol>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
