      "text": "A 45-year-old male presents to the emergency department with hematemesis and melena for the past 2 days. He reports long-term use of nonsteroidal anti-inflammatory drugs (NSAIDs) for chronic back pain. On examination, he is found to be pale and hypotensive. Upper gastrointestinal endoscopy reveals a bleeding duodenal ulcer, as shown below. Which artery is most likely involved in the bleeding?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Left gastric artery",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Gastroduodenal artery",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Splenic artery",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Common hepatic artery",
          "correct": false
        }
