      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:711px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Gastric <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">Ulcer</span> </strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Duodenal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">Ulcer</span> </strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Common risk factors for both GU and DU: H.pylori and <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"867d774b951692777190c8cfebd37a\">indiscriminate</span> use of NSAIDs.</li>\n<li>Epigastric pain, described as a burning or gnawing discomfort, can be present in both DU and GU</li>\n<li>Epigastric tenderness</li>\n<li>Tachycardia or Orthostasis: <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"998fb41ebc1692777202e46891c4a7\">Vomiting</span> may be due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4f75cbe5e8169277719615b86767c9\">pylorospasm</span> or local edema.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>The pain pattern in GU patients: Discomfort may be precipitated by food.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>The typical pain pattern in DU occurs 90 min to 3 hours after a meal and is frequently relieved by antacids or food.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>M/C site: Lesser curvature</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>M/C site: The first part of the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"280e59e9331692777186f3beac2c41\">duodenum</span> or <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"2257fb9f7f1692777186ff3e166b69\">duodenal cap</span> is usually within 3 cm of the pylorus.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Artery involved: Left <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">artery</span> <strong>(Option A)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Artery involved: <strong>Gastroduodenal <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a66cd3adaa1692777182e77cb23021\">artery</span> </strong><strong>(Option B)</strong></li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"Benign <span class=\" custommeta\"=\"\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\"/>gastric ulcer\" data-author=\"Ed Uthman, MD\" data-hash=\"9387\" data-license=\"Open Access\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Benign_gastric_ulcer_1.jpg\" data-tags=\"April2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/axhzD2Aw5nHIP3DPHEa41744372907.png\" />\n\t\t\t<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</figure>\n</div>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<div style=\"text-align:center\">\n<figure class=\"caption_element\" style=\"display:inline-block\"><img alt=\"Duodenal ulcer\" data-author=\"melvil\" data-hash=\"9388\" data-license=\"CC BY SA 4.0\" data-source=\"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Duodenal_ulcer01.jpg\" data-tags=\"April2025\" src=\"https://image.prepladder.com/notes/QotS7xj12m1bFekSjmSM1744373017.png\">\n<figcaption>{{caption_text}}</figcaption>\n</img></figure>\n</div>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
