    },
    {
      "text": "A 50-year-old male presents with a 3-month history of intermittent epigastric pain, nausea, and bloating. He has a history of duodenal ulcers diagnosed 5 years ago, which were treated with antacids. He reports occasional indigestion. Upper gastrointestinal endoscopy reveals a small duodenal ulcer. A biopsy confirms the presence of H. pylori infection. Which of the following conditions in this patient would warrant H. pylori eradication therapy? 1) Peptic ulcer disease (PUD) 2) Gastric lymphoma (MALT lymphoma) 3) Non-ulcer dyspepsia 4) Irritable bowel syndrome (IBS)",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "1, 2, 3, 4",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "2, 3, 4",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "1 and 2",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Only 1",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "C. 1 and 2",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>General recommendations</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Strong recommendations</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Functional dyspepsia.</li>\n<li>Chronic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7861e10657169277718815c2f42a75\">gastritis</span> with dyspepsia.</li>\n<li>Chronic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e627149ccc169277718241f723cc82\">atrophic gastritis</span> with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"8f88b9c691169277718754ca072062\">erosion</span> or intestinal metaplasia.</li>\n<li>Long-term use of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"9c823198d61692777196bc71097d6d\">proton</span> pump inhibitor.</li>\n<li>Family history of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> cancer (first-degree relatives with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> ulcer).</li>\n<li>After <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"17b5bd50d91692777197ea9cb7f468\">resection</span> of early <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> cancer.</li>\n<li>Long-term aspirin/NSAID medication history with <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f6768ff15f1692777195a493cad3a9\">peptic</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">ulcer</span> disease.</li>\n<li>H. pylori-related diseases (lymphocytic gastritis, <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> hyperplastic polyps, Menetrier disease).</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>Peptic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"7b4370a0b01692777201a5bc0739c2\">ulcer</span> disease.</li>\n<li>Gastric <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"62de0ec43c16927771912c01f6f373\">MALT</span> lymphoma.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
      "bot": "@dams_new_robot",
      "audio": "",
      "video": "",
      "uid": "6f6add59"
    },
    {
      "text": "A 45-year-old male with a history of peptic ulcer disease was treated with triple therapy (omeprazole, clarithromycin, and amoxicillin) for 14 days. Six weeks later, he presents with persistent epigastric discomfort. Which test is most appropriate to confirm the eradication of the causative organism?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Urea breath test",
          "correct": true
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "H. pylori serology",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Upper GI endoscopy",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Rapid urease test",
          "correct": false
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "A. Urea breath test",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Tests used to evaluate H.Pylori eradication</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Urea breath test</strong></p>\n<p><strong>(Option A)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>It is a simple, <strong>non-invasive, highly sensitive and specific test.</strong></li>\n<li>It is ideally performed <strong>at least 4 weeks after the completion of therapy</strong> to avoid any false negatives due to the <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"a459f313d9169277719789fdfb7ada\">residual</span> effects of antibiotics or PPIs.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Stool <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"782b31281a1692777181708484c1d1\">antigen</span> test</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>It is also a <strong>noninvasive</strong> test, and to avoid false negatives, it needs to be <strong>performed</strong> <strong>after 4</strong> <strong>weeks of treatment</strong>.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p><strong>Biopsy-based <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"ebf8f256f3169277718992ac1b2330\">histology</span> tests</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<ul>\n<li>It can be done to evaluate the success of the treatment.</li>\n<li>It can only be <strong>performed after 2 weeks of stopping PPIs and 6 weeks of stopping antibiotics.</strong></li>\n<li>It is not commonly preferred.</li>\n</ul>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
