    {
      "text": "A 52-year-old male with a history of peptic ulcer disease (PUD) is prescribed omeprazole, for the management of his condition. Which of the following is not an anticipated adverse effect of long-term PPI use?",
      "options": [
        {
          "label": "A",
          "text": "Stress fractures",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "B",
          "text": "Community acquired pneumonia",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "C",
          "text": "Chronic kidney disease",
          "correct": false
        },
        {
          "label": "D",
          "text": "Hypermagnesemia",
          "correct": true
        }
      ],
      "correct_answer": "D. Hypermagnesemia",
      "question_images": [],
      "explanation_images": [],
      "explanation": "<table cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"border-collapse:collapse; width:624px\">\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td colspan=\"2\" style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p style=\"text-align:center\"><strong>Adverse effects of long-term usage of <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"6d17c6d6f1169277719687447037f2\">PPI</span> </strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Acute <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"f46ba26d111692777190def3b1d80a\">interstitial</span> nephritis</p>\n<p>(AIN)</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Fever, eosinophilia, and decreased <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"0096f2a7631692777201eb9f21d5a7\">urine</span> output leading to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4cdc8161f71692777180df58cafa93\">Acute</span> <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4aa6035df41692777190b41d4a1583\">Kidney</span> Injury (AKI)</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Bone pain</p>\n<p><strong>(Option A ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Long-term PPIs increase the risk of <strong>osteoporosis and</strong> <strong>stress fractures.</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Clostridium difficile infections</p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Due to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"10c83adb331692777197f775bec1aa\">reduced</span> <strong>gastric acidity</strong>, which normally acts as a barrier to bacterial growth, there is increased risk of <strong>C. difficile infections</strong></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Community-Acquired Pneumonia</p>\n<p><strong>(Option B ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Increased <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"17cd3771bb1692777190950c142dbe\">incidence</span> for CAP is seen due to <strong>impaired <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"12347b15191692777188bc86d226e1\">gastric</span> defense</strong>, leading to <strong>increased bacterial colonization</strong> in the upper GI tract.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Chronic <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"4aa6035df41692777190b41d4a1583\">kidney</span> disease</p>\n<p><strong>(Option C ruled out)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Chronic or untreated AIN can progress to <span class=\"customMeta\" data-dictid=\"e6dc8586b11692777184b083672593\">CKD</span> over time.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>Hypomagnesemia</p>\n<p><strong>(Option D)</strong></p>\n</td>\n<td style=\"border-bottom:1px solid #000000; border-left:1px solid #000000; border-right:1px solid #000000; border-top:1px solid #000000; vertical-align:top\">\n<p>It can cause muscle cramps, tetany-like manifestations, and arrhythmias.</p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n\n\n<p style='font-size: 10px; color: #808080; font-style: italic;'></p>",
